 heal wounds'), (23, 'that Christian ritual cannot. After all my years in the art world, I have to say'), (24, 'that this claim'), (25, '-- that art brings peace that religion cannot'), (26, "-- is overblown and invalid. But it is a pretty conceit and it is the second main theme of this beautiful film.<br /><br />One last note: at Babette's arrival at the spinsters' home, a particular French general, Galliffet, is named as the person"), (27, "who in 1871 executed Babette's husband and son, and imposed a military rule that she had to flee. At the end of the film, as the General tells the story of the magnificent meal he enjoyed in Paris many years before (before 1871), at the conclusion of some military maneuvers, it turns out"), (28, 'that this same Galliffet was his host at the meal. As the General tells the story, French general Galliffet praised the chef of that meal as the greatest woman, the only woman'), (29, 'he would risk his life for. Of course, that woman was Babette. Thus, ironically, the same French general who said'), (30, 'he honored Babette above all other women was responsible for driving her away from France forever.')], 'Satellite', 'elaboration')
